    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2010-04-15</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2010-04-29T14:16:52Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>National Heroes Credit Protection Act - Amends the Servicemembers Civil Relief Act to authorize a servicemember, after having served on active duty for more than 180 days, to request that a consumer reporting agency (CRA) include in that servicemember's file a military service deployment alert. Requires the CRA to: (1) provide the alert to each person who requests the credit score or consumer report of such servicemember; and (2) develop and maintain procedures for referral of such alert to other CRAs.</p> <p>Requires: (1) a reseller of credit reporting information to include in any report on a servicemember any alert placed in such servicemember's file by another CRA; and (2) any user of a consumer credit report containing such alert to acknowledge to the servicemember the receipt of the alert.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
